1
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,929
-"Why did I get here late?"
-"Why did I get here late?"

2
00:00:15,765 --> 00:00:17,308
Well, I…

3
00:00:17,892 --> 00:00:20,228
I was in a relationship for about a year.

4
00:00:21,521 --> 00:00:23,064
-What?
-Huh?

5
00:00:24,399 --> 00:00:26,025
Seriously, that's cheating.

6
00:00:26,109 --> 00:00:28,361
Then you aren't an eternal single.

7
00:00:28,445 --> 00:00:30,697
A year? You're not an eternal single.

8
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:35,076
But…

9
00:00:36,036 --> 00:00:37,579
I never met her.

10
00:00:45,962 --> 00:00:48,047
What happened was,

11
00:00:48,131 --> 00:00:49,716
I started university during the pandemic.

12
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:52,302
I had no one to talk to, and I was lonely.

13
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:54,179
So I decided to talk to strangers.

14
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:55,847
I was bored at home, after all.

15
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:57,557
There was this anonymous chat app.

16
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:59,726
I met someone on it,

17
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:02,896
developed feelings for her,

18
00:01:02,979 --> 00:01:04,606
and we kept texting each other.

19
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:06,816
But when I asked to meet up,

20
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:10,487
she kept telling me excuses and said no.

21
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:12,947
Since it was my first time

22
00:01:13,031 --> 00:01:15,283
having a close connection with a woman,

23
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:17,494
I couldn't cut her off right away.

24
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:20,538
I thought we'd meet one day,
but it kept getting put off.

25
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:23,458
And a year passed like that.

26
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:26,294
This might sound strange,

27
00:01:26,377 --> 00:01:28,421
but I never got to see her
live and breathe.

28
00:01:31,216 --> 00:01:32,717
So it was an online relationship.

29
00:01:32,801 --> 00:01:33,968
A virtual relationship.

30
00:01:34,636 --> 00:01:38,681
Like how your characters
get married in online games?

31
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:40,642
Wow.

32
00:01:40,725 --> 00:01:41,893
You never saw her…

33
00:01:42,977 --> 00:01:43,937
in real life?

34
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:45,355
No, never.

35
00:01:45,438 --> 00:01:47,023
I kept trying to meet her,

36
00:01:47,106 --> 00:01:49,567
but she said she couldn't make the time

37
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:51,903
because of a family situation.

38
00:01:53,029 --> 00:01:55,990
-I couldn't go and call her out
-Right.

39
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:57,909
for telling lies.

40
00:01:57,992 --> 00:01:59,577
So I just trusted her

41
00:01:59,661 --> 00:02:01,913
and waited for about a year.

42
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:03,957
Still, how did he go a year
without meeting her?

43
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:06,126
Could it have been a man?

44
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:07,252
The other person…

45
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:10,713
-They must've talked on the phone.
-Maybe the person used a voice changer.

46
00:02:10,797 --> 00:02:12,882
Did he send her money? I hope he didn't.

47
00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:14,175
-I did check that.
-Good.

48
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,510
-He didn't.
-Thank goodness.

49
00:02:15,593 --> 00:02:18,847
In that case, I don't think
it's a big problem.

50
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,890
-Back in elementary school,
-Okay.

51
00:02:20,974 --> 00:02:22,809
I met girls online
through instant messenger.

52
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:25,979
-Did you date girls on the messenger?
-Yes.

53
00:02:26,062 --> 00:02:27,272
Without actually meeting?

54
00:02:27,355 --> 00:02:30,275
It's fine as long as he doesn't brag about
that dating experience.

55
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:33,528
-It's all in the past. Let it go.
-Okay.

56
00:02:33,611 --> 00:02:36,573
I don't think that counts
as a dating experience.

57
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:37,949
You're an eternal single.

58
00:02:38,908 --> 00:02:40,994
You're definitely qualified.

59
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:43,997
You meet the qualifications
to be on our show.

60
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,707
-Okay.
-You should work out some more.

61
00:02:45,790 --> 00:02:47,500
-Yeah, I'm working out hard.
-Good.

62
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:49,711
You should look cool and sharp
when you join them.

63
00:02:49,794 --> 00:02:51,296
Yes. I'm trying to get fit.

64
00:02:51,379 --> 00:02:54,132
-You're determined, right?
-I'm working hard to lose weight.

65
00:02:54,215 --> 00:02:57,719
Back in high school, I was very fat.

66
00:02:57,802 --> 00:03:00,513
I weighed almost 100 kg at one point.

67
00:03:00,597 --> 00:03:03,516
<i>My friends always told me to lose weight.</i>

68
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,351
<i>To meet someone nice,</i>

69
00:03:05,435 --> 00:03:08,146
<i>I thought I should be</i>
<i>physically attractive.</i>

70
00:03:08,229 --> 00:03:10,398
<i>So I worked hard to lose weight.</i>

71
00:03:12,901 --> 00:03:15,069
Now, I've gained some confidence.

72
00:03:15,778 --> 00:03:18,740
Compared to the other participants,

73
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:21,367
I have more experience
in talking to women.

74
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:22,535
He's bragging.

75
00:03:22,619 --> 00:03:24,037
I told you not to!

76
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:26,539
I think I'll do well

77
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:29,208
even if I join the show
later than the others.

78
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:33,171
LEE JIN-WOO
BEEN IN A ONE-YEAR ONLINE RELATIONSHIP

79
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:37,342
I guess that's why I joined you guys late.

80
00:03:40,845 --> 00:03:41,846
I see.

81
00:03:43,681 --> 00:03:46,726
<i>A one-year relationship? That's 365 days.</i>

82
00:03:46,809 --> 00:03:49,562
They passed the 100th-day mark
and even the 300th-day mark.

83
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:51,356
Isn't that pretty long?

84
00:03:52,106 --> 00:03:54,400
<i>He said he never met the woman.</i>

85
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:57,946
I think that makes him an eternal single.

86
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:00,782
<i>It still is a relationship.</i>

87
00:04:00,865 --> 00:04:02,909
In any case, he gave her his heart.

88
00:04:02,992 --> 00:04:05,620
They must've talked so much
throughout the year.

89
00:04:05,703 --> 00:04:07,080
I can't accept this.

90
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:09,540
No. He isn't an eternal single.

91
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:12,752
<i>If he'd met the woman in person,</i>
<i>I wouldn't have accepted him.</i>

92
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:14,629
But he never even met her in real life,

93
00:04:14,712 --> 00:04:16,756
so I accept him as an eternal single.

94
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:18,174
They're all divided.

95
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,467
They talk like judges.

96
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:21,261
They have a lot of pride
as eternal singles.

97
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:24,222
-I know.
-Yes. They have strict criteria.

98
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:27,475
It's a bit awkward.

99
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,521
Let me pick one.

100
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:36,150
"Who's most likely to have undergone
the biggest makeover?"

101
00:04:36,234 --> 00:04:38,444
-What? It must be another participant.
-What?

102
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:41,114
<i>-Again? Right away?</i>
-Someone else must be coming.

103
00:04:43,449 --> 00:04:44,575
-No way.
-It must be a woman.

104
00:04:45,076 --> 00:04:46,244
That's fast.

105
00:04:46,327 --> 00:04:48,204
It really is. It's moving so fast.

106
00:04:48,871 --> 00:04:50,832
There she comes.

107
00:04:51,499 --> 00:04:52,500
She's coming.

108
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:00,174
<i>Is it a girl?</i>

109
00:05:00,883 --> 00:05:01,718
<i>I'm so curious.</i>

110
00:05:04,554 --> 00:05:07,724
-Hello.
-Hello.

111
00:05:07,807 --> 00:05:09,309
-Hello.
-Welcome.

112
00:05:13,021 --> 00:05:14,939
<i>I thought she's so pretty.</i>

113
00:05:15,023 --> 00:05:18,484
<i>I wondered why she's an eternal single.</i>

114
00:05:19,068 --> 00:05:20,903
<i>She was simply pretty.</i>

115
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:22,322
<i>Look, Seung-hyun froze.</i>

116
00:05:26,868 --> 00:05:28,578
<i>She was stunning.</i>

117
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:30,621
<i>I'm in trouble.</i>

118
00:05:31,789 --> 00:05:33,833
I feel threatened.

119
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:37,670
<i>She was so beautiful</i>
<i>that I kept staring at her.</i>

120
00:05:39,213 --> 00:05:40,715
<i>Honestly, it made me nervous.</i>

121
00:05:40,798 --> 00:05:43,676
She was the epitome of feminine beauty,
in my opinion.

122
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:47,138
<i>So I felt quite threatened.</i>

123
00:05:48,389 --> 00:05:49,932
Hello.

124
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:52,602
Nice to meet you.

125
00:05:54,854 --> 00:05:56,105
She's gorgeous.

126
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:57,607
-She's beautiful.
-She's so pretty.

127
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:59,609
-Hello.
-Hello.

128
00:06:08,409 --> 00:06:09,577
Hold on a second.

129
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:10,870
I think he fell in love again.

130
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:12,246
Does he fall in love easily?

131
00:06:12,330 --> 00:06:13,706
He wears his heart on his sleeve.

132
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:22,381
Hello, I'm Han Su-ji,
a 26-year-old eternal single.

133
00:06:22,465 --> 00:06:25,176
I majored in illustration in the UK,

134
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:27,136
and I'm a ceramicist now.

135
00:06:30,389 --> 00:06:33,184
<i>I do a lot of independent work</i>

136
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:36,104
<i>that combines illustration and pottery.</i>

137
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:39,315
<i>I spend most of my time in my studio.</i>

138
00:06:39,398 --> 00:06:41,109
-Independent work.
-She works alone.

139
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:43,986
That leaves you
with no opportunities to meet men.

140
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:47,990
HAN SU-JI, CERAMICIST

141
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:51,661
I was in first or second grade

142
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:54,747
<i>when I moved to the UK.</i>

143
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:57,667
<i>After spending about five years there,</i>

144
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,627
<i>-I came back to Korea.</i>
<i>-How cute!</i>

145
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:02,547
Then I went to middle school
and high school in Korea

146
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:05,007
and went back to the UK for university.

147
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,801
<i>She lived abroad alone.</i>

148
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:10,930
I lived abroad on my own
for many years since I was young.

149
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:12,682
I also lived in the dorm for a long time.

150
00:07:12,765 --> 00:07:15,935
<i>So, I'm very independent.</i>

151
00:07:16,018 --> 00:07:18,813
<i>I think it can make me appear</i>

152
00:07:18,896 --> 00:07:22,024
<i>unapproachable in other people's eyes.</i>

153
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:24,694
Su-ji, this is the vibe I get from you.

154
00:07:24,777 --> 00:07:26,154
"I can do it by myself!"

155
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:28,239
"Don't come near me!"

156
00:07:28,739 --> 00:07:30,116
That's what I'm getting.

157
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:33,953
You're too perfect. You're like an AI.

158
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,206
Oh, no!

159
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:38,624
Ask for people's opinions.

160
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,710
-Don't try to do everything by yourself
-Right.

161
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:43,171
-like a wizard with a magic wand.
-Okay.

162
00:07:43,254 --> 00:07:45,673
My desire to date someone is at its max.

163
00:07:45,756 --> 00:07:46,966
It's at 100%.

164
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:49,760
I'll get a boyfriend this time.

165
00:07:49,844 --> 00:07:53,848
TO. MY FUTURE BOYFRIEND

166
00:08:05,485 --> 00:08:08,571
<i>I'll woo everyone with my charms.</i>

167
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:09,739
<i>Go, Su-ji!</i>

168
00:08:09,822 --> 00:08:10,781
<i>Let's do it!</i>

169
00:08:12,116 --> 00:08:13,659
You can sit where you want.

170
00:08:14,285 --> 00:08:16,245
Well, my towel…

171
00:08:17,538 --> 00:08:19,499
I need to check it.

172
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:36,766
Is it also "Why did I get here late?"

173
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:37,725
Maybe.

174
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:42,522
Please read it out loud.

175
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:44,524
-This is so much fun.
-It's a secret.

176
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,150
-It's a secret.
-Is it a secret?

177
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:47,360
Yes.

178
00:08:47,443 --> 00:08:48,819
It must be a personal question.

179
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:51,322
I'll keep it to myself.

180
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:53,950
-Come on. Why is it a secret?
-What is it?

181
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:55,493
Who should I pick?

182
00:08:55,576 --> 00:08:57,745
Is she giving it to the one she likes?

183
00:08:57,828 --> 00:09:00,164
-Already?
-But she only just got here.

184
00:09:00,248 --> 00:09:01,415
-What is it?
-What is it?

185
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:08,839
I feel like I'm getting scanned.

186
00:09:08,923 --> 00:09:10,841
-I know.
-She seems really torn.

187
00:09:12,176 --> 00:09:14,220
I've decided.

188
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:16,597
Check the question alone.

189
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:18,182
-Alone?
-Yes.

190
00:09:18,266 --> 00:09:19,392
It's a secret.

191
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:21,769
What is it?

192
00:09:21,852 --> 00:09:23,354
That's interesting.

193
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:25,147
-It must be a different one.
-Seems so.

194
00:09:25,856 --> 00:09:26,899
I'm curious.

195
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:33,573
She gave me the towel.

196
00:09:35,866 --> 00:09:39,704
<i>It read, "Who has</i>
<i>the best first impression?"</i>

197
00:09:39,787 --> 00:09:41,289
<i>His heart must've skipped a beat.</i>

198
00:09:41,372 --> 00:09:44,250
<i>The one with the best first impression was</i>

199
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:45,376
<i>Jung-yun.</i>

200
00:09:46,377 --> 00:09:48,004
<i>He just caught my eye.</i>

201
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:50,298
His vibe

202
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:53,426
and style stood out from the others.

203
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:58,055
<i>So I put the towel around Jung-yun's neck.</i>

204
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:03,603
<i>She gave me the towel.</i>

205
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:06,063
But I wasn't sure why.

206
00:10:06,147 --> 00:10:09,233
"Why? Why did she choose me?"

207
00:10:09,317 --> 00:10:11,652
Of course, I was happy.

208
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:14,614
<i>It was the most heart-fluttering</i>
<i>moment of the day.</i>

209
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:19,660
HAS YOUR TOP PICK CHANGED?

210
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:21,412
Yes.

211
00:10:21,912 --> 00:10:25,291
<i>I picked Han-ju</i>
<i>for the first impression vote.</i>

212
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:29,712
<i>Now, it's Su-ji.</i>

213
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:34,634
<i>Since Su-ji gave me the towel,</i>

214
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:36,802
<i>she caught my attention a bit more.</i>

215
00:10:36,886 --> 00:10:38,346
He changed his mind quickly.

216
00:10:38,429 --> 00:10:40,181
So quick. I love it.

217
00:10:43,559 --> 00:10:46,437
<i>I could see why they're game changers.</i>

218
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:48,522
A FEW DAYS LATER

219
00:10:49,106 --> 00:10:50,399
I'll call you <i>nuna</i> from now on.

220
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:51,609
<i>-Did you hear that?</i>
<i>-Seriously,</i>

221
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:53,444
<i>the game changers are taking over.</i>

222
00:10:53,527 --> 00:10:55,029
I bet you read Hyun-seo's diary.

223
00:10:55,112 --> 00:10:56,530
-Am I right?
-No.

224
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:58,032
-Whose, then?
-I read yours today.

225
00:10:58,115 --> 00:10:59,283
Did you?

226
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:01,160
<i>Su-ji is doing a proper job</i>
<i>as a game changer.</i>

227
00:11:01,243 --> 00:11:03,162
<i>She's stealing every man's heart.</i>

228
00:11:03,245 --> 00:11:05,790
<i>Oh my. Su-ji.</i>

229
00:11:06,374 --> 00:11:08,292
<i>Jin-woo is something else.</i>

230
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:10,086
<i>Absolutely game-changing.</i>

231
00:11:10,586 --> 00:11:13,881
<i>Will those two show</i>
<i>what's expected of the game changers?</i>

232
00:11:13,964 --> 00:11:15,132
Oh my. Su-ji.

233
00:11:15,216 --> 00:11:17,134
-What?
-The game changers seem to fit the title.

234
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:19,387
Seriously. This season's
game changers are something else.

235
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:22,973
Did Su-ji join late
because she has dating experience?

236
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:24,934
As far as I know, she has no experience.

237
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:27,019
She was born a game changer.

238
00:11:27,686 --> 00:11:29,397
Maybe her English name is Maggie,

239
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,816
similar to the Korean word
for "game changer."

240
00:11:32,608 --> 00:11:33,526
-Not bad.
-Maggie?

241
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:34,735
Yes, Maggie.

242
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:39,031
I wonder if anyone had a change of heart
after the game changers' entrance.

243
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:40,491
-I bet many people did.
-You think so?

244
00:11:40,574 --> 00:11:41,909
-I agree.
-Yes.

245
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:48,040
<i>For the first impression vote,</i>

246
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:50,209
<i>I picked Soo-hyun.</i>

247
00:11:50,292 --> 00:11:51,836
<i>But it wasn't like</i>

248
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:54,713
I've had a conversation with her.

249
00:11:54,797 --> 00:11:57,425
<i>On the other hand,</i>
<i>I had dinner with Hyun-seo.</i>

250
00:11:57,508 --> 00:11:59,510
<i>She expressed her interest first as well.</i>

251
00:12:00,136 --> 00:12:03,806
So now, I'm leaning more toward Hyun-seo.

252
00:12:14,108 --> 00:12:15,693
Honestly, I had a change of heart.

253
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:19,155
As I spent time with everyone
throughout the day,

254
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:22,616
<i>I got to talk to them</i>
<i>and learned how they interact.</i>

255
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:23,909
<i>That made me change my mind.</i>

256
00:12:24,493 --> 00:12:26,912
Currently, my top pick

257
00:12:27,496 --> 00:12:28,873
<i>is Choi Hyuk-joon.</i>

258
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:30,916
Right.

259
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:36,380
<i>I think I felt that romantic attraction.</i>

260
00:12:37,673 --> 00:12:40,050
<i>And my second pick</i>

261
00:12:40,634 --> 00:12:41,594
<i>is Jae-seo.</i>

262
00:12:42,845 --> 00:12:44,263
What? Wow.

263
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:48,225
I found him very entertaining.

264
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:50,853
That piqued my curiosity.

265
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:52,980
-She found him entertaining.
-What a relief.

266
00:12:53,063 --> 00:12:54,982
-Jae-seo has a chance.
-He does.

267
00:12:55,065 --> 00:12:57,026
Jae-seo had received zero votes.

268
00:12:57,109 --> 00:12:58,694
But "entertaining…"

269
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:01,363
I'm an entertaining person too.

270
00:13:02,781 --> 00:13:03,824
-Still.
-Will it get anywhere?

271
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:05,326
-It means something.
-Her curiosity

272
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:07,953
might turn into an interest
which might turn into love.

273
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:09,622
-It can spark something.
-Yes.

274
00:13:09,705 --> 00:13:10,873
-It's still half a vote.
-Zero point five.

275
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:12,791
-Zero point five.
-Let's put it that way.

276
00:13:13,459 --> 00:13:14,335
KIM JAE-SEO
FIRST IMPRESSION PICK: SEO-YOON

277
00:13:14,418 --> 00:13:16,629
<i>My top pick is definitely Seo-yoon.</i>

278
00:13:16,712 --> 00:13:17,963
<i>He hasn't changed his mind.</i>

279
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:20,132
<i>I didn't have a change of heart.</i>

280
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:23,469
<i>I haven't had a chance to talk</i>

281
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:25,846
<i>to Jung-yun.</i>

282
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:27,973
<i>On the other hand,</i>

283
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:30,351
<i>Hyuk-joon and I shared a meal,</i>

284
00:13:30,434 --> 00:13:32,061
<i>and I got to know him better.</i>

285
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:35,773
So I'm more drawn to Hyuk-joon now.

286
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:43,155
Currently, my top pick is Hyuk-joon.

287
00:13:43,656 --> 00:13:46,617
-Hyuk-joon received many votes.
-Right. He got all the votes.

288
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:48,953
But his heart is with someone else.

289
00:13:49,036 --> 00:13:50,037
-Exactly.
-He likes Hyun-seo.

290
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:52,623
-As they talked and eased up,
-Right.

291
00:13:52,706 --> 00:13:54,250
they must've developed feelings.

292
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:55,668
-They're eternal singles, after all.
-Right.

293
00:13:55,751 --> 00:13:58,295
I didn't expect their picks
to change so quickly.

294
00:13:58,379 --> 00:13:59,755
In Season One…

295
00:13:59,838 --> 00:14:01,215
-Exactly.
-Wasn't it much slower?

296
00:14:01,298 --> 00:14:02,132
That's right.

297
00:14:02,216 --> 00:14:05,427
I think it's because the producers
designed the system very well.

298
00:14:05,511 --> 00:14:07,680
-It's very nicely designed, right?
-Yes, indeed.

299
00:14:07,763 --> 00:14:09,431
-It's great.
-Everything is intense.

300
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:20,776
Oh, hey.

301
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:24,488
I didn't know where to go, so here I am.

302
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:26,657
-We're playing a game.
-We're playing a game.

303
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,117
-Join us. Yes.
-Really?

304
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:33,497
Oh, but they just left,
so I think they'll be a while…

305
00:14:33,581 --> 00:14:35,457
-I'll join you guys.
-Okay.

306
00:14:36,792 --> 00:14:38,043
May I sit here?

307
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:39,295
-Yes.
-Yes, of course.

308
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:44,675
Specific or unusual qualities
we look for in a partner.

309
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:46,635
-That's what we were talking about.
-Do you have any?

310
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:50,097
I'm not saying this is a must.

311
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:53,225
But if he wears this item,
he'll get bonus points.

312
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:54,768
If he wears this item, I'll love it.

313
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:56,353
Glasses.

314
00:14:57,813 --> 00:15:01,775
I really like men
who can pull off glasses.

315
00:15:02,484 --> 00:15:04,194
Nerd vibes, I guess.

316
00:15:04,278 --> 00:15:06,488
-Oh, I see.
-Right, I get the idea.

317
00:15:07,656 --> 00:15:09,992
I like women who enjoy manga.

318
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:12,411
Do you like manga?

319
00:15:12,494 --> 00:15:15,873
Yes, I love manga, especially <i>Digimon</i>.

320
00:15:15,956 --> 00:15:18,000
-Hyun-seo is obsessed with manga.
-So…

321
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:20,169
I hope my girlfriend
will like manga as well.

322
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:21,754
I bet he earned points there.

323
00:15:21,837 --> 00:15:23,839
I'm certain he did.

324
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,925
-Someone who smiles a lot.
-A smiley person.

325
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:29,136
-And--
-Your perfume.

326
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,722
-What?
-I think I recognize it.

327
00:15:31,805 --> 00:15:33,182
Another 13.

328
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:37,311
-It goes well with your outfit.
-Thanks.

329
00:15:37,394 --> 00:15:41,607
Apparently, some people
find this scent unpleasant.

330
00:15:41,690 --> 00:15:42,733
Right.

331
00:15:42,816 --> 00:15:44,109
-Do you like it?
-Yes.

332
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:46,028
That's why I'm surprised.

333
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:49,406
I found it unpleasant
when I smelled it on someone else.

334
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:51,784
But it smells good on you.

335
00:15:51,867 --> 00:15:53,452
I guess each person… What was it called?

336
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:56,372
I didn't really like that perfume.

337
00:15:57,539 --> 00:15:59,416
<i>But I found it pleasant</i>
<i>for the very first time.</i>

338
00:16:00,709 --> 00:16:04,171
I guess this perfume was made
for someone like her.

339
00:16:04,254 --> 00:16:06,048
He seems really giddy.

340
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:08,300
Which perfume do you use?

341
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:09,259
Well…

342
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:13,430
-Would you like a sniff?
-Oh, sure.

343
00:16:15,349 --> 00:16:16,684
What's going on?

344
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:21,146
That's a move
that makes your heart flutter.

345
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:23,065
Is it okay to use that move
just like that?

346
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:25,067
No, he shouldn't.

347
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:30,322
It's a woody fragrance.

348
00:16:30,406 --> 00:16:32,074
-It smells nice.
-It's…

349
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:33,242
Which brand is it?

350
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:34,576
TAMBURINS.

351
00:16:36,078 --> 00:16:37,162
So you like perfume.

352
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:38,497
Yes, I really like perfume.

353
00:16:39,081 --> 00:16:40,249
Me too.

354
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:43,961
<i>She's also into perfume,</i>

355
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:46,296
and the scent I don't like
smells good on her.

356
00:16:46,380 --> 00:16:49,550
I'm self-conscious about my voice,
but she has a nice voice.

357
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:52,136
Could this be fate?

358
00:16:52,219 --> 00:16:54,054
You know… How should I put it?

359
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:57,808
I think one's voice is
an important part of their identity.

360
00:16:57,891 --> 00:16:58,726
You're right.

361
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:02,062
So, as soon as I heard your voice,
I found you really cool.

362
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:03,647
-Really?
-Yes, seriously.

363
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:06,275
<i>For real,</i>

364
00:17:06,358 --> 00:17:08,694
I didn't actually say the words,
but I basically said I like her.

365
00:17:08,777 --> 00:17:10,029
"I like your clothes."

366
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:11,447
"I like your voice too."

367
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:13,323
"You have good taste in perfume too."

368
00:17:13,907 --> 00:17:16,785
<i>Also, I pulled out the chair for her.</i>

369
00:17:18,245 --> 00:17:19,621
-Did he pull it out?
-What did he do?

370
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:22,124
-Oh, just now.
-He pulled out his chair.

371
00:17:25,294 --> 00:17:27,463
It was like… How should I put it?

372
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:29,548
I went all out.

373
00:17:29,631 --> 00:17:32,593
Like a full-scale offensive
from a helicopter.

374
00:17:32,676 --> 00:17:35,054
<i>Every little detail</i>

375
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:37,306
<i>about her is perfect.</i>

376
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:39,099
Her voice, her aura,

377
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:42,269
her outfit, her perfume…
Everything was perfect.

378
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:45,105
She checked all my boxes.

379
00:17:45,814 --> 00:17:47,357
I guess I believe in fate.

380
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:50,944
<i>Oh, I don't know.</i>
<i>Is it because of the environment we're in?</i>

381
00:17:51,028 --> 00:17:53,822
<i>I can already feel myself changing.</i>

382
00:17:55,407 --> 00:17:57,159
How many hours has it been again?

383
00:17:57,242 --> 00:17:59,244
-Less than a day.
-Only a few hours.

384
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:01,830
Fate, marriage…

385
00:18:01,914 --> 00:18:03,373
Doesn't that remind you of someone?

386
00:18:05,918 --> 00:18:07,044
He's getting ahead of himself.

387
00:18:07,127 --> 00:18:10,464
-I can see how Hyuk-joon feels, but…
-I know. He fell head over heels for her.

388
00:18:10,547 --> 00:18:12,883
Hyun-seo may be an eternal single,
but wouldn't she have noticed

389
00:18:12,966 --> 00:18:15,719
that Hyuk-joon likes her?
He made it too obvious.

390
00:18:15,803 --> 00:18:17,137
-I'm sure of it.
-Definitely.

391
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:20,849
They share three interests.

392
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:21,934
Manga.

393
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:23,227
-Voice.
-Voice.

394
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:24,394
-Fragrance.
-Perfume.

395
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:25,687
-They click.
-What do you think?

396
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:27,689
A guy who identifies
your perfume right away.

397
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:29,274
To be honest,

398
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:31,985
a man who knows so well about perfumes

399
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:33,862
-seems like a womanizer.
-Right?

400
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:36,323
-I'd be a little put off.
-Right?

401
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:38,951
-I asked because I thought so too.
-Right.

402
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:40,744
You had Bon Dosirak?

403
00:18:41,703 --> 00:18:42,704
"Bon Dosirak."

404
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:44,289
-<i>Dakgalbi</i> and pork.
-<i>Dakgalbi.</i>

405
00:18:44,373 --> 00:18:45,624
-And pork.
-That's right.

406
00:18:45,707 --> 00:18:48,085
-Along with some <i>gim</i>.
-He's an expert.

407
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:49,211
I could tell right away.

408
00:18:52,005 --> 00:18:54,508
-<i>Season Two is proceeding so fast.</i>
-<i>It's moving fast.</i>

409
00:18:54,591 --> 00:18:55,843
<i>-Yes.</i>
<i>-I love it.</i>

410
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:58,846
I'm worried some of them
might try to kiss on day two.

411
00:18:58,929 --> 00:19:00,264
I'm so nervous.

412
00:19:03,976 --> 00:19:05,060
Post Office?

413
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:06,603
ETERNAL SINGLES' POST OFFICE IS OPEN
PLEASE OPEN YOUR CABINET

414
00:19:06,687 --> 00:19:08,730
-"Please open your cabinet."
-Post Office?

415
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:11,108
What's this?

416
00:19:11,191 --> 00:19:12,943
<i>Where is the Post Office?</i>

417
00:19:13,569 --> 00:19:15,070
-Do you see it?
-It's here.

418
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:16,905
-It's here.
-It's open.

419
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:19,241
They must've planned
about 260 things for them to do.

420
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:22,035
It's the most important.

421
00:19:22,619 --> 00:19:24,037
Can we all go in at once?

422
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:24,955
Wow.

423
00:19:25,038 --> 00:19:26,165
Can we go in all together?

424
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:30,544
<i>-There are a lot of things.</i>
<i>-Many cute things.</i>

425
00:19:30,627 --> 00:19:31,753
ETERNAL SINGLES' POST OFFICE

426
00:19:31,837 --> 00:19:33,338
<i>They can write a letter if they want.</i>

427
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:35,799
Oh, take a look at this.

428
00:19:35,883 --> 00:19:37,843
There are instructions.

429
00:19:37,926 --> 00:19:40,762
"Eternal Singles' Post Office is
a 24-hour unmanned post office."

430
00:19:40,846 --> 00:19:44,600
"With three Gift Coupons,
you can purchase the item you want."

431
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:47,186
"Use the cabinets
to express your feelings."

432
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:51,815
Cookies…

433
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:53,066
Earrings.

434
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:54,860
-There's a <i>Dol Hareubang </i>lip balm.
-What?

435
00:19:54,943 --> 00:19:56,653
There are perfumes too.

436
00:19:56,737 --> 00:19:57,946
The bracelets are cute.

437
00:19:58,030 --> 00:20:00,949
-I kind of want this.
-Don't you want this lucky charm?

438
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,994
<i>If I make good use of this,</i>

439
00:20:04,077 --> 00:20:08,707
it could help me express my feelings.

440
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:10,918
Is there something inside?

441
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:14,713
<i>There's a letter inside.</i>

442
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:22,554
It's a message from the Cupid.

443
00:20:22,638 --> 00:20:23,889
I don't know if I can show it.

444
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:25,515
Why is it so short?

445
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:27,392
NOTHING TO SAY TO YOU
WHY? BECAUSE YOU'RE PERFECT

446
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:28,727
That's nice.

447
00:20:28,810 --> 00:20:30,729
-That's what I like.
-I know.

448
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:32,397
There's more.

449
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:34,107
-There's more?
-A collection of dad jokes.

450
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:35,776
A COLLECTION OF DAD JOKES
BY CAR, THE GARDEN

451
00:20:37,277 --> 00:20:39,947
"What separates men from women?
The 'from'."

452
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:41,907
I don't even know what to say.

453
00:20:41,990 --> 00:20:44,660
Why did they read it?
It was supposed to give him an edge.

454
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:46,828
-It's too much, right?
-It's too much.

455
00:20:47,829 --> 00:20:49,581
<i>I'll never use the jokes.</i>

456
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:51,833
People were completely shocked.

457
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:53,961
So it'd be a disaster
if I actually used it.

458
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:56,004
-I won't use it at all costs.
-Why?

459
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,005
It's perfect.

460
00:20:58,799 --> 00:21:00,092
HOW ARE THE MALE PARTICIPANTS?

461
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:01,635
<i>I was so grateful.</i>

462
00:21:01,718 --> 00:21:03,136
<i>Because…</i>

463
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:05,055
Well, someone

464
00:21:05,138 --> 00:21:07,307
-received a two-sentence letter.
-"Someone."

465
00:21:07,391 --> 00:21:11,019
<i>But Han-na put in the effort</i>
<i>and wrote me a long letter.</i>

466
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:13,272
<i>I was very grateful.</i>

467
00:21:13,355 --> 00:21:14,314
<i>Jin-woo.</i>

468
00:21:15,148 --> 00:21:17,609
<i>He advised me to be honest</i>
<i>about my feelings</i>

469
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:21,029
<i>instead of getting swayed</i>
<i>by other people's feelings.</i>

470
00:21:21,113 --> 00:21:22,698
His message really encouraged me.

471
00:21:24,658 --> 00:21:25,867
<i>"You'll do well."</i>

472
00:21:25,951 --> 00:21:28,412
-<i>Reading that message made me tear up.</i>
-Why?

473
00:21:28,495 --> 00:21:31,748
<i>It really moved my heart.</i>

474
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,542
MY LOVELY SU-JI,
HAVE THE BEST TIME

475
00:21:33,625 --> 00:21:35,294
Thank you.

476
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:37,504
-Now…
-What?

477
00:21:39,047 --> 00:21:41,383
DATE SELECTION WILL SOON BEGIN
FEMALE ETERNAL SINGLES, GATHER AROUND

478
00:21:41,466 --> 00:21:42,968
Female eternal singles will choose!

479
00:21:43,051 --> 00:21:44,678
<i>-Will they go on a date?</i>
<i>-It'll begin now.</i>

480
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:46,680
-Oh my gosh!
-<i>Now comes the real deal.</i>

481
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:51,601
Did you get the text?

482
00:21:51,685 --> 00:21:52,853
Did you? Did you read it?

483
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:53,812
I read it.

484
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:58,817
Arm wrestling competition?

485
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:00,319
ARM WRESTLING COMPETITION

486
00:22:00,402 --> 00:22:02,946
"Today, the male eternal singles'
arm wrestling competition…"

487
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:04,197
"…will determine your date."

488
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:06,992
"Female eternal singles,
guess the ranking of your desired date

489
00:22:07,075 --> 00:22:08,952
and put your photocard in the slot."

490
00:22:09,036 --> 00:22:11,955
They need to guess the men's rankings.

491
00:22:12,039 --> 00:22:13,623
It'll be fun to place a bet.

492
00:22:13,707 --> 00:22:15,834
-I know.
-If their desired dates seem strong,

493
00:22:15,917 --> 00:22:17,586
they'll bet on a higher rank.

494
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:18,754
Otherwise,

495
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:21,006
-they'll bet on a lower rank.
-Right.

496
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:22,341
-Rock-paper-scissors!
-Scissors!

497
00:22:23,508 --> 00:22:24,968
-I'll go first.
-Okay.

498
00:22:25,052 --> 00:22:27,512
PREDICTION ORDER: HAN-JU, HYUN-SEO,
SOO-HYUN, SU-JI, SEO-YOON

499
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:31,183
-I'll choose third place.
-Third place?

500
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:35,353
<i>The guys on my mind were</i>
<i>Hyuk-joon and Jin-woo.</i>

501
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:38,982
Neither one seemed particularly strong,

502
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:42,903
<i>so I figured betting on third place</i>
<i>would get me one of the two.</i>

503
00:22:45,322 --> 00:22:47,657
I'll choose second place.

504
00:22:48,241 --> 00:22:51,745
<i>I thought Seung-hyun could place second,</i>

505
00:22:51,828 --> 00:22:53,371
<i>so I put my photocard there.</i>

506
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:56,583
I'll choose first place.

507
00:22:58,376 --> 00:22:59,544
You trust him.

508
00:22:59,628 --> 00:23:00,504
For now, yes.

509
00:23:01,129 --> 00:23:03,048
<i>I wanted to get to know</i>

510
00:23:03,131 --> 00:23:05,342
Hyuk-joon or Jae-seo.

511
00:23:05,425 --> 00:23:08,845
They're both tall and look strong,

512
00:23:08,929 --> 00:23:13,100
so I thought one of them would place first

513
00:23:13,183 --> 00:23:14,559
and put my photocard there.

514
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,770
The same number as my order. Fourth place.

515
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:19,898
I'll keep it simple and trust my luck.

516
00:23:19,981 --> 00:23:21,566
5TH PLACE

517
00:23:21,650 --> 00:23:22,818
All done.

518
00:23:23,401 --> 00:23:25,362
ARM WRESTLING COMPETITION
PLAY ROCK-PAPER-SCISSORS TO DECIDE THE BYE

519
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:27,322
AFTER THE MATCH,
THE LOSERS COMPETE FOR 4TH AND 5TH PLACES

520
00:23:27,906 --> 00:23:28,907
That's so funny.

521
00:23:28,990 --> 00:23:30,826
Men could see this

522
00:23:30,909 --> 00:23:33,870
and strategize
depending on the date they want.

523
00:23:33,954 --> 00:23:35,622
-On purpose?
-They might do that

524
00:23:35,705 --> 00:23:37,749
-since we made our selections first.
-How fun!

525
00:23:37,833 --> 00:23:40,252
-Hyun-seo is smart.
-That's right.

526
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:43,755
Will the men see the women's selections
before the arm wrestling?

527
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:45,006
-I think so.
-They will.

528
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:48,426
Male participants need to remember
that it's not about winning.

529
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:50,095
-You're right.
-They need to think.

530
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:52,180
If you want Hyun-seo,
who chose second place,

531
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:54,891
-you must place second, not anything else.
-That's right.

532
00:23:54,975 --> 00:23:57,394
Instead of focusing on
beating the opponent,

533
00:23:57,477 --> 00:23:59,563
-they should use their brains.
-They should think.

534
00:23:59,646 --> 00:24:03,525
Eternal singles tend to get unnecessarily
worked up in certain situations.

535
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:07,654
Here come the players.

536
00:24:09,781 --> 00:24:11,658
-Arm wrestling?
-Arm wrestling?

537
00:24:12,868 --> 00:24:15,162
-They want us to use our muscles already.
-I know.

538
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:19,332
<i>Frankly, I became very flustered</i>
<i>when I saw what we had to do.</i>

539
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:23,670
I thought it was too soon
for a strength contest.

540
00:24:24,254 --> 00:24:28,091
I just thought
I shouldn't make a fool of myself.

541
00:24:28,884 --> 00:24:29,968
This is…

542
00:24:30,051 --> 00:24:32,304
<i>When I saw the board,</i>

543
00:24:32,387 --> 00:24:34,306
<i>I saw that Hyun-seo</i>
<i>had chosen second place.</i>

544
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:36,683
<i>I needed to take second place, so…</i>

545
00:24:36,766 --> 00:24:41,104
I thought I should put in the effort
and get a date with her.

546
00:24:41,188 --> 00:24:43,982
Hyuk-joon needs to rank pretty high.

547
00:24:44,065 --> 00:24:46,109
"Play rock-paper-scissors
to decide the bye

548
00:24:46,193 --> 00:24:47,402
and proceed with the matches."

549
00:24:47,485 --> 00:24:49,863
"The losers compete
for fourth and fifth places."

550
00:24:50,864 --> 00:24:52,657
-Shall we play rock-paper-scissors?
-All right.

551
00:24:52,741 --> 00:24:54,367
-Play or lose, rock-paper-scissors!
-Rock-paper-scissors!

552
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:56,578
Oh, you got a bye!

553
00:24:56,661 --> 00:24:57,579
You got it right away.

554
00:24:58,205 --> 00:25:00,540
-Then the one who got a bye…
-He advanced automatically.

555
00:25:00,624 --> 00:25:02,959
-Is that Jung-yun? He got a bye.
-Yes. Jung-yun.

556
00:25:04,377 --> 00:25:09,132
The ones I wanted to talk to

557
00:25:09,716 --> 00:25:12,135
were Jung-yun

558
00:25:12,219 --> 00:25:13,303
and Seung-hyun.

559
00:25:13,386 --> 00:25:17,933
<i>Since one of them got a bye and advanced,</i>

560
00:25:18,016 --> 00:25:20,101
<i>I hoped I'd at least get Seung-hyun.</i>

561
00:25:20,894 --> 00:25:22,062
I wonder who'll place first.

562
00:25:22,145 --> 00:25:23,104
I'm curious too.

563
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:25,815
-Let's begin.
-Shall we?

564
00:25:25,899 --> 00:25:27,150
-Shall we begin?
-Okay.

565
00:25:27,234 --> 00:25:30,111
1ST PRELIMINARY MATCH
JIN-WOO VERSUS JAE-SEO

566
00:25:30,695 --> 00:25:32,322
<i>He has a strong build.</i>

567
00:25:32,405 --> 00:25:34,199
Should I take this off too?

568
00:25:34,866 --> 00:25:36,534
<i>When I learned that we were arm wrestling,</i>

569
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:38,161
I thought, "Not bad."

570
00:25:38,245 --> 00:25:40,413
Jae-seo is like a gangster!

571
00:25:41,831 --> 00:25:42,707
"Gangster."

572
00:25:42,791 --> 00:25:44,292
He has a fighter's eyes.

573
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:46,044
How will he do?

574
00:25:46,628 --> 00:25:48,129
<i>At first glance,</i>

575
00:25:48,213 --> 00:25:50,423
<i>Jae-seo looked the strongest.</i>

576
00:25:50,507 --> 00:25:53,760
I thought I'd be able to beat
everyone else if I could beat him.

577
00:25:55,053 --> 00:25:56,054
I haven't done this…

578
00:26:02,686 --> 00:26:04,104
<i>-You can tell from the grip.</i>
<i>-Yeah.</i>

579
00:26:04,187 --> 00:26:05,063
<i>The moment you grab</i>…

580
00:26:07,857 --> 00:26:09,317
-Shall we do this?
-Yes.

581
00:26:09,401 --> 00:26:12,570
<i>Arm wrestling in front of women</i>
<i>you've just met is quite…</i>

582
00:26:14,864 --> 00:26:16,116
-Start when I blow the whistle.
-Okay.

583
00:26:19,244 --> 00:26:20,328
Oh, hey! Wait!

584
00:26:22,038 --> 00:26:23,206
Oh, hey! Wait!

585
00:26:26,209 --> 00:26:27,627
-So humiliating.
-It ended so quickly.

586
00:26:29,421 --> 00:26:31,923
He didn't even get a chance
to use his strength.

587
00:26:33,049 --> 00:26:35,927
Gosh, that's so humiliating.

588
00:26:36,011 --> 00:26:38,638
-It's a bad look.
-Right.

589
00:26:38,722 --> 00:26:41,141
He let out a groan without even realizing.

590
00:26:41,224 --> 00:26:43,351
-He went, "Wait!"
-He couldn't hold it in.

591
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:45,562
"Hey!" When you say that, it's a bit…

592
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:48,106
It's not that. The arm…

593
00:26:48,189 --> 00:26:49,524
It's so embarrassing.

594
00:26:52,485 --> 00:26:55,071
<i>I didn't expect Jae-seo</i>
<i>to be eliminated so quickly.</i>

595
00:26:55,155 --> 00:26:57,991
As I saw that, I went, "What?"

596
00:26:58,575 --> 00:27:01,244
He lost very quickly.
It was quite unexpected.

597
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:06,541
Now, the next match.

598
00:27:09,210 --> 00:27:10,545
Grab each other's hand.

599
00:27:10,628 --> 00:27:11,463
You guys look cool.

600
00:27:12,255 --> 00:27:13,340
Hyun-seo's men.

601
00:27:13,423 --> 00:27:15,300
Hyun-seo's two men will compete.

602
00:27:20,555 --> 00:27:22,223
CHOI HYUK-JOON
TOP PICK: HYUN-SEO

603
00:27:22,307 --> 00:27:23,641
<i>I was the most worried about him.</i>

604
00:27:23,725 --> 00:27:26,770
I was 100% sure
that he had picked Hyun-seo,

605
00:27:26,853 --> 00:27:30,732
so I entered the match
with determination to win.

606
00:27:31,316 --> 00:27:32,400
He needs to advance.

607
00:27:32,484 --> 00:27:35,904
But Seung-hyun doesn't look weak.

608
00:27:36,404 --> 00:27:38,073
AHN SEUNG-HYUN
TOP PICK: HYUN-SEO

609
00:27:38,156 --> 00:27:39,199
<i>I…</i>

610
00:27:39,282 --> 00:27:42,160
want to go on a date
with Hyun-seo or Soo-hyun.

611
00:27:42,243 --> 00:27:44,329
If things don't… If I do badly…

612
00:27:45,413 --> 00:27:46,456
it'll be embarrassing.

613
00:27:48,124 --> 00:27:49,459
So I want to do well,

614
00:27:50,168 --> 00:27:53,046
but that doesn't mean
I'll actually do well.

615
00:27:54,672 --> 00:27:57,634
<i>I just went into the match</i>
<i>thinking I should do my best.</i>

616
00:27:57,717 --> 00:28:00,011
<i>-The two of them must…</i>
<i>-They must win.</i>

617
00:28:00,762 --> 00:28:01,679
Get ready.

618
00:28:08,019 --> 00:28:08,978
It's cutthroat.

619
00:28:12,732 --> 00:28:15,527
<i>-Oh my.</i>
<i>-He's holding out.</i>

620
00:28:15,610 --> 00:28:18,154
<i>What will happen? Will he hold out?</i>

621
00:28:18,238 --> 00:28:20,031
<i>-Will he?</i>
<i>-He must win.</i>

622
00:28:22,033 --> 00:28:23,034
Oh my gosh.

623
00:28:29,707 --> 00:28:31,042
He's good.

624
00:28:33,461 --> 00:28:34,587
So sad.

625
00:28:35,630 --> 00:28:37,424
I'm all drained.

626
00:28:38,007 --> 00:28:39,884
Even if you are, I'll still lose.

627
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:45,390
-Ready?
-Yes.

628
00:28:45,473 --> 00:28:46,641
Be careful not to hurt your elbow.

629
00:28:46,725 --> 00:28:47,642
Get ready.

630
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:54,441
I'm no match for him.

631
00:28:56,192 --> 00:28:57,402
I'm no match for him.

632
00:28:58,153 --> 00:28:59,487
I'm no match for him.

633
00:29:01,406 --> 00:29:02,699
What? I mean…

634
00:29:03,199 --> 00:29:05,827
Well, Jae-seo is looking a bit…

635
00:29:05,910 --> 00:29:07,787
-The winner has been decided.
-Yes.

636
00:29:09,622 --> 00:29:10,749
Thanks for the match.

637
00:29:10,832 --> 00:29:11,833
-Yes.
-Thank you.

638
00:29:14,252 --> 00:29:16,838
5TH PLACE
SEO-YOON AND JAE-SEO

639
00:29:17,422 --> 00:29:18,923
-Are you okay?
-Yes.

640
00:29:19,007 --> 00:29:20,300
I have very weak arms.

641
00:29:21,259 --> 00:29:22,385
Look how thin my wrist is.

642
00:29:23,094 --> 00:29:25,096
-No, maybe it was a strategy.
-It's good for Jae-seo.

643
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:27,432
-Maybe that was his strategy.
-It worked out for him.

644
00:29:27,515 --> 00:29:29,392
-Wait. You're right.
-Maybe it was a strategy.

645
00:29:29,476 --> 00:29:31,561
-To go on a date with Seo-yoon?
-That must be it.

646
00:29:31,644 --> 00:29:32,854
He must've planned it.

647
00:29:32,937 --> 00:29:35,273
He should go on a date and say
that he lost on purpose.

648
00:29:35,356 --> 00:29:36,816
That'd be better. I like that idea.

649
00:29:38,109 --> 00:29:41,946
<i>To be honest, I saw</i>
<i>Seo-yoon's photocard at fifth place.</i>

650
00:29:44,199 --> 00:29:45,575
Arm wrestling?

651
00:29:47,035 --> 00:29:47,911
Arm wrestling.

652
00:29:48,828 --> 00:29:51,706
<i>I saw her photocard at fifth place,</i>

653
00:29:51,790 --> 00:29:54,751
and the results didn't matter
to me anymore.

654
00:29:54,834 --> 00:29:57,712
<i>I wanted to go on a date with Seo-yoon,</i>

655
00:29:57,796 --> 00:29:59,088
<i>so I put on a show.</i>

656
00:29:59,172 --> 00:30:02,675
<i>I pretended to be humiliated</i>

657
00:30:02,759 --> 00:30:04,969
<i>so that it wouldn't look too obvious.</i>

658
00:30:05,595 --> 00:30:07,096
Hold on a second. You know…

659
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:08,765
Hold on.

660
00:30:08,848 --> 00:30:11,893
You know, it's a bit…

661
00:30:11,976 --> 00:30:13,561
You want to fact-check, don't you?

662
00:30:13,645 --> 00:30:15,772
There's no such thing as
"pretending" to be humiliated.

663
00:30:15,855 --> 00:30:17,857
His reaction
during the first match seemed real.

664
00:30:17,941 --> 00:30:19,400
-That's a lie.
-He was like, "Oh!"

665
00:30:20,318 --> 00:30:21,444
He's lying, right?

666
00:30:22,070 --> 00:30:24,072
-It's not what I think it is, right?
-Let it go.

667
00:30:24,155 --> 00:30:26,741
-Okay, I'll let it go.
-Let's protect his pride.

668
00:30:26,825 --> 00:30:28,743
4TH PLACE
SU-JI AND SEUNG-HYUN

669
00:30:32,121 --> 00:30:33,456
<i>I was quite stressed.</i>

670
00:30:33,540 --> 00:30:36,668
In my opinion, Su-ji is

671
00:30:36,751 --> 00:30:38,503
quite threatening.

672
00:30:38,586 --> 00:30:41,047
<i>After all, she's so pretty.</i>

673
00:30:41,130 --> 00:30:43,383
<i>I thought that if Seung-hyun</i>
<i>went on a date with Su-ji,</i>

674
00:30:44,342 --> 00:30:47,762
<i>he might drift away from me.</i>

675
00:30:49,848 --> 00:30:51,766
Play or lose, rock-paper-scissors.

676
00:30:52,350 --> 00:30:53,184
Yes.

677
00:30:53,268 --> 00:30:54,352
HYUK-JOON ADVANCES TO THE FINAL

678
00:30:54,435 --> 00:30:55,979
Oh, a bye.

679
00:30:59,399 --> 00:31:01,651
-I need to do it again.
-I don't feel confident.

680
00:31:07,824 --> 00:31:09,409
It looks like he works out a lot.

681
00:31:09,492 --> 00:31:10,702
Look at his lats.

682
00:31:10,785 --> 00:31:12,495
-He has impressive lats.
-I know.

683
00:31:13,496 --> 00:31:17,125
<i>I didn't know this</i>
<i>when he had his jacket on,</i>

684
00:31:17,208 --> 00:31:19,377
<i>but it turns out he has impressive lats.</i>

685
00:31:19,460 --> 00:31:21,087
<i>That's when I realized</i>
<i>I'd underestimated him.</i>

686
00:31:21,170 --> 00:31:22,672
<i>It looked like Jin-woo</i>
<i>would take first place.</i>

687
00:31:22,755 --> 00:31:24,382
<i>I made the wrong decision.</i>

688
00:31:24,465 --> 00:31:26,843
I think people who work out regularly

689
00:31:26,926 --> 00:31:29,762
take good care of themselves.

690
00:31:29,846 --> 00:31:31,431
So, it won a bonus point from me.

691
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:35,476
Gosh, you've got a pretty strong grip.

692
00:31:36,394 --> 00:31:37,353
You're strong.

693
00:31:38,521 --> 00:31:39,689
Get ready.

694
00:31:45,778 --> 00:31:47,447
Wow!

695
00:31:50,241 --> 00:31:51,451
A leftie sure is different.

696
00:31:52,118 --> 00:31:54,329
3RD PLACE
HAN-JU AND JUNG-YUN

697
00:31:54,412 --> 00:31:56,456
Jin-woo will advance. He wants to advance.

698
00:31:56,539 --> 00:31:58,124
Looks like he wants to advance.

699
00:31:58,207 --> 00:32:00,001
He doesn't want to lose.

700
00:32:00,084 --> 00:32:01,127
-I'm a leftie.
-Okay.

701
00:32:01,210 --> 00:32:02,295
FINAL MATCH
JIN-WOO VERSUS HYUK-JOON

702
00:32:04,005 --> 00:32:05,798
-I'll use my left hand.
-Get ready.

703
00:32:07,717 --> 00:32:10,887
-I'm in trouble.
-<i>Hyuk-joon needs to lose this time.</i>

704
00:32:12,639 --> 00:32:14,307
-Are you ready?
-Yes.

705
00:32:14,390 --> 00:32:15,516
Are you ready?

706
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:16,434
-Yes.
-Yes.

707
00:32:18,519 --> 00:32:19,520
Get ready.

708
00:32:27,779 --> 00:32:28,821
We have a winner.

709
00:32:29,614 --> 00:32:30,907
He's no joke.

710
00:32:30,990 --> 00:32:31,866
He's insane.

711
00:32:33,952 --> 00:32:36,037
<i>It worked out for Hyuk-joon.</i>

712
00:32:37,080 --> 00:32:37,956
<i>Nicely done.</i>

713
00:32:38,873 --> 00:32:41,501
<i>I was determined to place second,</i>

714
00:32:41,584 --> 00:32:43,127
so I didn't put in much strength.

715
00:32:43,211 --> 00:32:44,712
I was over the moon.

716
00:32:44,796 --> 00:32:46,297
I even double-checked.

717
00:32:46,381 --> 00:32:48,633
I was like, "It's her, right?"

718
00:32:49,133 --> 00:32:51,678
1ST PLACE
SOO-HYUN AND JIN-WOO

719
00:32:52,220 --> 00:32:53,304
WHY DID YOU GO FOR THE FIRST PLACE?

720
00:32:53,388 --> 00:32:55,765
To be honest, I wanted to go on
a date with Su-ji.

721
00:32:55,848 --> 00:32:59,060
So I wondered if I should hold back,

722
00:32:59,143 --> 00:33:03,064
but I beat them all
when I didn't even try much.

723
00:33:03,147 --> 00:33:05,483
Before I even wondered
if I should hold myself back…

724
00:33:06,317 --> 00:33:08,820
I might sound cocky, but I beat everyone.

725
00:33:09,821 --> 00:33:10,863
So I went along with it.

726
00:33:11,656 --> 00:33:13,491
Maybe he just wanted to beat everyone.

727
00:33:13,574 --> 00:33:14,701
That's why he's excited.

728
00:33:14,784 --> 00:33:15,994
-Yes.
-He's excited that he won.

729
00:33:16,077 --> 00:33:17,245
What's the point, though?

730
00:33:19,747 --> 00:33:21,457
SOO-HYUN & JIN-WOO
HYUN-SEO & HYUK-JOON

731
00:33:21,541 --> 00:33:23,292
HAN-JU & JUNG-YUN
SU-JI & SEUNG-HYUN, SEO-YOON & JAE-SEO

732
00:33:25,336 --> 00:33:28,589
<i>"Starting with the winner,</i>
<i>pick a date plan in order."</i>

733
00:33:28,673 --> 00:33:31,926
It feels like it's really starting now.
I'm a bit nervous.

734
00:33:32,010 --> 00:33:33,386
-Are you nervous?
-Yes, a bit.

735
00:33:33,970 --> 00:33:35,471
<i>Paintball. Partner dancing?</i>

736
00:33:35,555 --> 00:33:37,181
<i>Those are some good options.</i>

737
00:33:37,890 --> 00:33:39,058
-Shall I choose first?
-Yes.

738
00:33:39,142 --> 00:33:40,143
Paintball.

739
00:33:41,102 --> 00:33:42,854
Partner dancing is a bit…

740
00:33:42,937 --> 00:33:44,689
I choose paintball as well.

741
00:33:44,772 --> 00:33:46,941
Here comes another hardship.

742
00:33:47,442 --> 00:33:49,527
Show us the dance moves after the date.

743
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:50,778
Absolutely not.

744
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:51,988
PAINTBALL
JIN-WOO, HYUK-JOON, JUNG-YUN

745
00:33:52,071 --> 00:33:53,031
PARTNER DANCING
SEUNG-HYUN, JAE-SEO

746
00:33:53,114 --> 00:33:55,616
-It might be better than expected.
-I think it'll be nice.

747
00:33:55,700 --> 00:33:57,076
-It sounds fun.
-Yeah.

748
00:33:57,660 --> 00:33:58,828
Who is it?

749
00:33:58,911 --> 00:34:00,288
-What do you mean?
-Who is it?

750
00:34:00,371 --> 00:34:01,497
I mean, your date.

751
00:34:03,207 --> 00:34:04,459
To be honest…

752
00:34:05,376 --> 00:34:07,462
Hey! How could you forget that?

753
00:34:12,884 --> 00:34:13,843
But…

754
00:34:15,094 --> 00:34:17,472
-Wasn't it… Wasn't it Hyun-seo?
-Fourth place?

755
00:34:17,555 --> 00:34:19,057
Is it Hyun-seo?

756
00:34:19,140 --> 00:34:20,683
Second place is going with Hyun-seo.

757
00:34:20,767 --> 00:34:21,851
She picked second place?

758
00:34:23,227 --> 00:34:26,981
I thought Hyun-seo
had chosen fourth place.

759
00:34:27,065 --> 00:34:30,443
So I was glad
that I'd get to talk to her again.

760
00:34:30,526 --> 00:34:32,445
But it wasn't her.

761
00:34:33,029 --> 00:34:34,572
What's wrong with him?

762
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:37,366
-Car, the garden, why…
-He's a bit…

763
00:34:37,450 --> 00:34:39,202
Here's what I think.

764
00:34:39,285 --> 00:34:41,370
-Tell us. What's wrong with him?
-He has

765
00:34:41,454 --> 00:34:43,372
a bit of trouble focusing.

766
00:34:44,040 --> 00:34:45,249
He gets easily distracted.

767
00:34:45,333 --> 00:34:48,044
He often goes, "What was it?"
He can't remember things.

768
00:34:48,127 --> 00:34:51,297
What if he meets Su-ji and goes,

769
00:34:51,380 --> 00:34:53,883
"Why… Why are you here?"

770
00:34:53,966 --> 00:34:55,593
If he does that…

771
00:34:55,676 --> 00:34:57,470
-If he asked, "Who is your date?" then…
-Exactly.

772
00:34:57,553 --> 00:34:59,138
He won't do that. Let me make a guess.

773
00:34:59,222 --> 00:35:01,265
"You know, you're so pretty."

774
00:35:01,849 --> 00:35:03,309
-No.
-"I'm startled."

775
00:35:03,392 --> 00:35:05,186
You're trying to protect him here.

776
00:35:05,269 --> 00:35:06,562
What do you mean?

777
00:35:08,272 --> 00:35:09,982
I'm a bit…

778
00:35:10,066 --> 00:35:12,193
Well, from the photocard…

779
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:15,780
<i>I couldn't tell who was who.</i>

780
00:35:16,739 --> 00:35:18,950
<i>I realized I got them mixed up</i>
<i>after talking to Jae-seo.</i>

781
00:35:19,033 --> 00:35:20,076
So…

782
00:35:20,159 --> 00:35:21,577
That's what happened.

783
00:35:22,578 --> 00:35:23,412
Yes.

784
00:35:28,292 --> 00:35:31,254
SOO-HYUN AND JIN-WOO
JIN-WOO CHOSE THE PAINTBALL DATE

785
00:35:32,255 --> 00:35:33,381
I'll go and change.

786
00:35:35,007 --> 00:35:37,176
<i>Since it was the first date,</i>

787
00:35:37,260 --> 00:35:39,595
I had worn feminine clothes.

788
00:35:39,679 --> 00:35:42,974
I was waiting in a skirt and tights.

789
00:35:44,517 --> 00:35:47,395
-Yes. Her mom told her to do that.
-That's right.

790
00:35:47,979 --> 00:35:49,605
-Then…
-Can I go in my pajamas?

791
00:35:50,815 --> 00:35:51,941
Did you get a text? What's your date?

792
00:35:52,024 --> 00:35:52,859
Well…

793
00:35:53,484 --> 00:35:55,987
"Kim Jae-seo chose…"

794
00:35:56,070 --> 00:35:57,321
-What?
-What is it?

795
00:35:57,405 --> 00:35:58,990
He chose partner dancing.

796
00:35:59,907 --> 00:36:02,702
Isn't this too much?

797
00:36:04,537 --> 00:36:05,997
I'll enjoy paintball.

798
00:36:06,080 --> 00:36:07,540
Jin-woo, thank you so much.

799
00:36:07,623 --> 00:36:09,458
-"Now…"
-Oh, Jin-woo…

800
00:36:09,542 --> 00:36:11,419
-What's this?
-I can get changed a hundred times.

801
00:36:12,211 --> 00:36:13,546
I could change a hundred times.

802
00:36:13,629 --> 00:36:15,298
<i>I'm so worried.</i>

803
00:36:16,340 --> 00:36:17,675
This is going to be fun.

804
00:36:18,259 --> 00:36:21,429
Going on the first date as a group
is less intimidating

805
00:36:21,512 --> 00:36:23,306
-for the eternal singles.
-That's right.

806
00:36:23,389 --> 00:36:25,725
If they start with a one-on-one date…
You know what would happen.

807
00:36:25,808 --> 00:36:28,019
-They'll mess up left and right.
-It's a no-no.

808
00:36:28,102 --> 00:36:31,480
They need to go as a group
to minimize the risks.

809
00:36:31,564 --> 00:36:32,398
PAINTBALL DATE

810
00:36:32,481 --> 00:36:34,150
<i>Let's hit the road.</i>

811
00:36:34,233 --> 00:36:35,693
<i>-Okay.</i>
<i>-Okay.</i>

812
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:38,487
Gosh, it's hot.

813
00:36:38,571 --> 00:36:41,157
Are you confident in your shooting skills?

814
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,116
Shooting.

815
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:44,035
-Shooting?
-You must've done it before.

816
00:36:44,118 --> 00:36:44,952
Well…

817
00:36:45,953 --> 00:36:48,998
Well, you might not like me talking about
my days in the army, but…

818
00:36:49,081 --> 00:36:50,708
I want to know if you're good at it.

819
00:36:51,542 --> 00:36:53,044
Well, I was

820
00:36:53,127 --> 00:36:54,545
a Special Warrior.

821
00:36:56,505 --> 00:36:58,049
-Were you a Special Warrior?
-Yes.

822
00:36:58,132 --> 00:36:59,800
I was a Special Warrior.

823
00:36:59,884 --> 00:37:02,011
Can I trust you?
Can we beat everyone else?

824
00:37:04,597 --> 00:37:06,766
You did look strong earlier.

825
00:37:06,849 --> 00:37:08,643
I don't know what to expect
from paintball.

826
00:37:08,726 --> 00:37:10,311
We suddenly need
clothes that can get dirty.

827
00:37:11,479 --> 00:37:12,521
He must be sweaty.

828
00:37:13,147 --> 00:37:15,233
-He must be warm.
-He must be feeling warm.

829
00:37:15,316 --> 00:37:17,276
Right, he sweats a lot.

830
00:37:20,404 --> 00:37:21,364
<i>My goodness.</i>

831
00:37:21,447 --> 00:37:23,115
<i>Oh, no. That's bad.</i>

832
00:37:23,199 --> 00:37:25,952
-Do you get hot easily?
-It's so hot in here.

833
00:37:26,452 --> 00:37:28,996
-Is it hot?
-The AC is on back here.

834
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,915
-Oh my. He's…
-Maybe turn on the front AC too.

835
00:37:30,998 --> 00:37:32,833
Is it because he's nervous?

836
00:37:32,917 --> 00:37:35,753
-You're sweating buckets.
-I…

837
00:37:35,836 --> 00:37:37,838
-I'm sweating so much.
-Shall I turn on the AC?

838
00:37:38,714 --> 00:37:41,425
<i>I was determined to win</i>
<i>because it's the first date,</i>

839
00:37:41,509 --> 00:37:43,261
<i>so I was nervous and anxious.</i>

840
00:37:43,344 --> 00:37:44,595
<i>He must be upset.</i>

841
00:37:44,679 --> 00:37:46,305
<i>You sweat more when you're nervous.</i>

842
00:37:46,973 --> 00:37:48,266
-Yesterday,
-Yes?

843
00:37:48,349 --> 00:37:50,726
-you said you like manga.
-Yes.

844
00:37:50,810 --> 00:37:53,938
Do you read it regularly?

845
00:37:54,021 --> 00:37:57,275
I watch anime and read manga all the time.

846
00:37:57,358 --> 00:38:00,027
I've watched <i>Jujutsu Kaisen</i>
multiple times.

847
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:01,988
You like <i>Jujutsu Kaisen?</i>

848
00:38:02,071 --> 00:38:04,699
Yes. But <i>Digimon </i>is my favorite.

849
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:08,160
You must've cried a lot
while watching the last <i>Digimon </i>movie.

850
00:38:08,744 --> 00:38:09,745
That's right.

851
00:38:09,829 --> 00:38:13,207
-As soon as I watched it…
-It's bound to make you cry.

852
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:15,418
Yes. I was bawling from the very start.

853
00:38:15,960 --> 00:38:20,464
I remember the scene where Agumon says,

854
00:38:20,548 --> 00:38:22,216
-"You're all grown up."
-Exactly.

855
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:23,259
It had me bawling.

856
00:38:25,052 --> 00:38:27,596
Oh, do people cry while watching <i>Digimon</i>?

857
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:30,266
-Of course. It's sad. Very sad.
-Really?

858
00:38:30,349 --> 00:38:31,809
It's heartbreaking.

859
00:38:31,892 --> 00:38:34,520
-It's a story about friendship and growth.
-And love.

860
00:38:35,104 --> 00:38:37,356
I don't understand
what they're talking about.

861
00:38:37,940 --> 00:38:39,734
Why did you watch
<i>Jujutsu Kaisen </i>multiple times?

862
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:42,611
I found Satoru Gojo really cool.

863
00:38:42,695 --> 00:38:44,280
Is he your favorite?

864
00:38:44,363 --> 00:38:45,948
Yuta Okkotsu is.

865
00:38:46,949 --> 00:38:48,534
If I may ask, who is your favorite?

866
00:38:48,617 --> 00:38:49,452
Mine is…

867
00:38:51,996 --> 00:38:54,165
-Kento and…
-Oh, Kento?

868
00:38:54,248 --> 00:38:55,333
Toji and…

869
00:38:55,916 --> 00:38:56,959
Suguru.

870
00:38:57,043 --> 00:38:59,962
-You like the sexy characters.
-That's right.

871
00:39:00,046 --> 00:39:01,297
I see.

872
00:39:03,341 --> 00:39:06,302
He said he likes women who like manga.

873
00:39:06,802 --> 00:39:10,264
We seem to have similar interests,

874
00:39:10,348 --> 00:39:12,016
so I was attracted to him.

875
00:39:12,099 --> 00:39:16,270
We really click in a lot of ways.

876
00:39:16,354 --> 00:39:18,814
So, I'd like to

877
00:39:19,482 --> 00:39:21,233
get to know him better.

878
00:39:21,317 --> 00:39:23,944
<i>I've grown curious about him.</i>

879
00:39:25,196 --> 00:39:27,323
No wonder he won a lot of brownie points.

880
00:39:27,406 --> 00:39:28,866
Definitely. It's pretty big.

881
00:39:28,949 --> 00:39:29,784
-It excites you.
-Yes.

882
00:39:29,867 --> 00:39:32,411
-"We can go on these dates."
-"What should we do next?"

883
00:39:32,495 --> 00:39:34,747
-Your imagination runs wild.
-That's right.

884
00:39:34,830 --> 00:39:36,290
-That's right.
-It gets you excited.

885
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:39,043
The date has already begun
for the two of them.

886
00:39:39,126 --> 00:39:40,795
I'm scared he might propose
to her tomorrow.

887
00:39:40,878 --> 00:39:42,505
-He's head over heels for her.
-Yes.

888
00:39:42,588 --> 00:39:44,006
I feel like

889
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:46,759
Han-ju might be listening in
from the back.

890
00:39:46,842 --> 00:39:48,177
Like, "What are they talking about?"

891
00:39:50,805 --> 00:39:53,265
Hyuk-joon drove,

892
00:39:53,349 --> 00:39:55,393
and Jin-woo sat in the back.

893
00:39:55,476 --> 00:39:58,896
<i>To be honest, I wasn't entirely</i>
<i>focused on Jung-yun.</i>

894
00:39:58,979 --> 00:40:01,857
<i>I kept listening in on the conversations</i>
<i>at the front and back.</i>

895
00:40:01,941 --> 00:40:03,651
I just felt jealous.

896
00:40:04,235 --> 00:40:06,695
That's right. All three women
wanted Hyuk-joon.

897
00:40:06,779 --> 00:40:08,114
<i>Hyuk-joon drove, right?</i>

898
00:40:08,197 --> 00:40:10,533
Hyuk-joon drove,
and I sat all the way in the back.

899
00:40:10,616 --> 00:40:13,869
I could still see him
since he was at the very front.

900
00:40:13,953 --> 00:40:16,622
<i>He seemed to be having fun</i>
<i>talking to Hyun-seo,</i>

901
00:40:16,705 --> 00:40:19,708
<i>so I thought,</i>
<i>"It must be a fun conversation."</i>

902
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:23,379
<i>Look at the entrance.</i>

903
00:40:23,462 --> 00:40:24,880
<i>The entrance is something else.</i>

904
00:40:24,964 --> 00:40:27,216
-It looks so intimidating.
-So scary.

905
00:40:27,299 --> 00:40:29,385
Are we enlisting in the military?

906
00:40:29,468 --> 00:40:30,803
Gosh, this is intense.

907
00:40:32,471 --> 00:40:35,474
<i>-It's paintball. The one with guns.</i>
<i>-So they'll actually do this.</i>

908
00:40:35,558 --> 00:40:37,059
<i>They're doing this for real.</i>

909
00:40:37,143 --> 00:40:38,519
<i>Gosh, this is really…</i>

910
00:40:39,145 --> 00:40:41,689
<i>The men will look really cool</i>
<i>if they protect their dates like a knight.</i>

911
00:40:42,523 --> 00:40:44,442
<i>Here we are. Paintball center.</i>

912
00:40:44,525 --> 00:40:47,153
<i>Let me briefly explain the rules.</i>

913
00:40:47,236 --> 00:40:51,115
<i>If a woman takes a bullet on the front</i>
<i>or back of the torso protector,</i>

914
00:40:51,198 --> 00:40:54,368
<i>the entire team is out.</i>

915
00:40:54,452 --> 00:40:55,703
<i>If you run out of bullets,</i>

916
00:40:56,287 --> 00:40:58,789
<i>you can get more supplies</i>
<i>on the battlefield.</i>

917
00:40:59,331 --> 00:41:01,041
The men need to protect their dates.

918
00:41:01,125 --> 00:41:03,836
The men won't get eliminated
even if they take multiple bullets,

919
00:41:03,919 --> 00:41:05,671
so they must throw themselves
for their partners.

920
00:41:05,754 --> 00:41:06,964
-That's right.
-Nice rules.

921
00:41:07,047 --> 00:41:09,717
-I agree.
-If they didn't have to protect the women,

922
00:41:10,301 --> 00:41:12,136
the men would've started
talking about the army

923
00:41:12,219 --> 00:41:14,346
-and gotten excited by themselves.
-Yeah.

924
00:41:14,430 --> 00:41:17,475
And naturally, it'll lead
to some physical contact.

925
00:41:17,558 --> 00:41:19,477
-Yes. Saying stuff like, "Come here."
-They'll hold hands.

926
00:41:19,560 --> 00:41:20,895
-I'm excited about this.
-Good.

927
00:41:20,978 --> 00:41:23,564
You know, the battlefield is

928
00:41:23,647 --> 00:41:24,940
-pretty small.
-You're right.

929
00:41:25,024 --> 00:41:28,110
It'll end if someone runs over and shoots.

930
00:41:28,194 --> 00:41:30,905
-Then shall we go on the offensive?
-Yes.

931
00:41:30,988 --> 00:41:32,823
-On the offensive?
-Yes.

932
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:34,241
Gosh, but…

933
00:41:34,909 --> 00:41:36,118
Just spray and pray.

934
00:41:37,703 --> 00:41:40,873
I love shooter games and stuff.

935
00:41:40,956 --> 00:41:46,629
We played paintball
on the ground with thick bushes.

936
00:41:46,712 --> 00:41:49,757
"Let's adopt a strategy
from <i>PUBG: Battlegrounds</i>."

937
00:41:49,840 --> 00:41:54,136
"Let's attack them from here."
I came up with plans like that.

938
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:56,138
<i>-Hyun-seo is competitive.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

939
00:41:56,222 --> 00:41:59,183
-Let's shoot them if they come here.
-Okay.

940
00:41:59,266 --> 00:42:01,101
-Stand behind me.
-Okay.

941
00:42:01,185 --> 00:42:03,437
I'll shoot while you stay in the back.

942
00:42:03,979 --> 00:42:06,398
I wonder how everyone is strategizing.

943
00:42:06,482 --> 00:42:08,025
TEAM PINK HELMET
JUNG-YUN AND HAN-JU

944
00:42:08,484 --> 00:42:11,904
Since the women need
to avoid getting shot,

945
00:42:11,987 --> 00:42:14,615
the men will try to protect them.

946
00:42:15,491 --> 00:42:18,536
Just like couple dodgeball,

947
00:42:18,619 --> 00:42:21,705
<i>we had to protect our partners.</i>

948
00:42:21,789 --> 00:42:25,125
I was a Special Warrior
during my military service.

949
00:42:25,209 --> 00:42:28,170
<i>"I was good at shooting.</i>
<i>It can't be so different."</i>

950
00:42:28,254 --> 00:42:31,882
I told myself that
to stay confident and focused.

951
00:42:31,966 --> 00:42:33,968
Judging by his looks,

952
00:42:34,051 --> 00:42:37,388
I wondered
if I should protect him instead.

953
00:42:37,471 --> 00:42:40,307
But since he said
that he was a Special Warrior,

954
00:42:40,391 --> 00:42:42,476
I felt like I could count on him.

955
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:44,270
Let's put our faith
in the Special Warrior.

956
00:42:44,353 --> 00:42:45,688
Gosh, I'm nervous.

957
00:42:45,771 --> 00:42:47,690
I'll do my best to protect you.

958
00:42:49,316 --> 00:42:50,651
I'll trust you.

959
00:42:51,318 --> 00:42:52,778
Let's avoid placing last.

960
00:42:52,861 --> 00:42:54,446
Let's place first. Okay.

961
00:42:56,949 --> 00:42:58,993
-Let's not get hurt.
-It's so scary.

962
00:42:59,076 --> 00:43:00,703
-Good luck.
-Good luck.

963
00:43:01,954 --> 00:43:03,163
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

964
00:43:03,247 --> 00:43:04,331
-Which way?
-Where do we go?

965
00:43:04,415 --> 00:43:06,041
Just take a pick. I don't care either way.

966
00:43:06,542 --> 00:43:08,002
HYUK-JOON, HYUN-SEO

967
00:43:08,085 --> 00:43:09,420
They're coming.

968
00:43:09,503 --> 00:43:11,171
-Are they coming this way?
-Hold on.

969
00:43:13,257 --> 00:43:15,342
-Did you see her sidestepping out?
-Yes.

970
00:43:15,426 --> 00:43:16,343
-She's good.
-Seriously.

971
00:43:16,927 --> 00:43:18,137
She looked like a pro.

972
00:43:18,721 --> 00:43:20,264
-Are they coming this way?
-Hold on.

973
00:43:20,347 --> 00:43:22,683
HYUK-JOON, HYUN-SEO

974
00:43:22,766 --> 00:43:23,851
JUNG-YUN, HAN-JU

975
00:43:23,934 --> 00:43:25,519
What should we do? Shall we watch?

976
00:43:25,603 --> 00:43:27,104
-Let's watch and see.
-Okay.

977
00:43:30,816 --> 00:43:32,776
-Shall we get down?
-Okay.

978
00:43:33,569 --> 00:43:35,112
Shall we fire some warning shots?

979
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:41,201
He's shooting.

980
00:43:41,285 --> 00:43:43,329
HYUN-SEO, HYUK-JOON

981
00:43:47,791 --> 00:43:49,251
<i>Nice stance.</i>

982
00:43:51,420 --> 00:43:54,214
HAN-JU, JUNG-YUN

983
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:56,091
<i>What are they shooting at?</i>

984
00:43:56,759 --> 00:43:58,552
JUNG-YUN, JIN-WOO

985
00:44:00,596 --> 00:44:02,640
Gosh, my flank hurts.

986
00:44:06,935 --> 00:44:09,021
-Over there.
-How many bullets do you have left?

987
00:44:09,104 --> 00:44:11,440
Oh, I've got none left.

988
00:44:11,523 --> 00:44:13,484
Shall we go to the center?

989
00:44:13,567 --> 00:44:15,694
Looks like we need to. Oh, no.

990
00:44:15,778 --> 00:44:17,404
-I have some left.
-I was blasting like crazy.

991
00:44:17,488 --> 00:44:19,031
We should hurry up, right?

992
00:44:19,114 --> 00:44:20,866
Please lead the way.

993
00:44:20,949 --> 00:44:23,952
JUNG-YUN, HAN-JU

994
00:44:26,080 --> 00:44:27,164
Hold on.

995
00:44:30,709 --> 00:44:33,212
HYUN-SEO

996
00:44:35,214 --> 00:44:36,507
It stings!

997
00:44:37,132 --> 00:44:38,300
Shall we retreat?

998
00:44:38,384 --> 00:44:39,593
-Retreat, a bit at a time.
-Okay.

999
00:44:41,845 --> 00:44:43,138
We'll need to run away.

1000
00:44:44,932 --> 00:44:46,892
Don't we need more bullets?

1001
00:44:46,975 --> 00:44:48,352
-What was that?
-Bullets.

1002
00:44:48,435 --> 00:44:49,603
-We need them,
-Okay.

1003
00:44:49,687 --> 00:44:51,063
but we might get hit on our way.

1004
00:44:51,814 --> 00:44:54,525
I mean, he won't get eliminated
even if he takes a hit.

1005
00:44:54,608 --> 00:44:56,193
Men don't get eliminated.

1006
00:44:56,860 --> 00:44:59,279
-He wants to avoid the pain.
-"We might get hit on our way."

1007
00:44:59,363 --> 00:45:01,573
HAN-JU

1008
00:45:04,243 --> 00:45:05,327
Gosh, it stings.

1009
00:45:05,411 --> 00:45:06,328
You got hit on the head.

1010
00:45:09,164 --> 00:45:10,457
Oh, gosh.

1011
00:45:10,541 --> 00:45:12,418
-Gosh.
-Gosh, that hurts.

1012
00:45:13,001 --> 00:45:14,378
Oh, it stings!

1013
00:45:18,090 --> 00:45:19,842
It hurts. It kind of stings.

1014
00:45:19,925 --> 00:45:21,051
Oh, it stings!

1015
00:45:21,135 --> 00:45:22,261
"Oh, it stings"?

1016
00:45:22,344 --> 00:45:24,721
-That's a bit…
-Was he really a Special Warrior?

1017
00:45:24,805 --> 00:45:25,973
Oh, it stings!

1018
00:45:26,515 --> 00:45:28,058
Ouch, it stings!

1019
00:45:28,934 --> 00:45:29,852
WHEN DID YOU FIND YOURSELF COOL?

1020
00:45:29,935 --> 00:45:32,980
<i>When bullets came flying toward us,</i>
<i>I had to protect her.</i>

1021
00:45:33,063 --> 00:45:35,107
So I plucked up my courage

1022
00:45:35,190 --> 00:45:37,734
and told Han-ju to stand behind me

1023
00:45:37,818 --> 00:45:40,195
so that she wouldn't get hit.

1024
00:45:40,279 --> 00:45:43,991
I shielded her with my body.

1025
00:45:46,785 --> 00:45:48,954
<i>I think I was</i>

1026
00:45:49,037 --> 00:45:51,039
a bit of a heartthrob

1027
00:45:52,207 --> 00:45:53,292
in that moment.

1028
00:45:53,375 --> 00:45:54,376
What?

1029
00:45:54,460 --> 00:45:56,003
What is he talking about?

1030
00:45:56,086 --> 00:45:59,423
He didn't exactly look cool.

1031
00:45:59,506 --> 00:46:03,343
Jung-yun said he was a Special Warrior
during his military service,

1032
00:46:03,427 --> 00:46:04,803
<i>and he shielded me from the bullets.</i>

1033
00:46:05,429 --> 00:46:06,638
-Oh, no.
-I got hit on my arm.

1034
00:46:06,722 --> 00:46:08,474
-I didn't get hit on the body, right?
-No.

1035
00:46:10,017 --> 00:46:11,226
She got hit all over.

1036
00:46:11,310 --> 00:46:13,187
Oh, it stings!

1037
00:46:13,270 --> 00:46:16,857
But since I was taking multiple hits,

1038
00:46:16,940 --> 00:46:19,568
I thought he wasn't up to par.

1039
00:46:19,651 --> 00:46:22,154
I didn't get butterflies.

1040
00:46:23,655 --> 00:46:25,949
-Of course not.
-There wasn't a heartthrob moment.

1041
00:46:26,033 --> 00:46:28,744
His reaction was a bit too cute
when he took a hit.

1042
00:46:28,827 --> 00:46:29,661
"Oh, it stings!"

1043
00:46:29,745 --> 00:46:33,540
-"Oh, it stings!"
-"Oh, it stings!"

1044
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:34,583
HYUN-SEO, HYUK-JOON

1045
00:46:34,666 --> 00:46:36,460
We should take out Team Pink first.

1046
00:46:41,340 --> 00:46:43,467
Shall we go this way? This way.

1047
00:46:43,550 --> 00:46:46,178
HYUN-SEO

1048
00:46:46,261 --> 00:46:47,888
<i>Why is Hyun-seo so into it?</i>

1049
00:46:48,847 --> 00:46:50,599
<i>She's running right toward them.</i>

1050
00:46:51,558 --> 00:46:53,644
-She's the Special Warrior!
-Yes.

1051
00:46:53,727 --> 00:46:56,772
HYUN-SEO

1052
00:46:57,606 --> 00:46:58,982
<i>She's zeroing in on the target.</i>

1053
00:46:59,066 --> 00:47:00,317
I think she got hit.

1054
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:01,777
Oh, I took a hit.

1055
00:47:02,861 --> 00:47:05,614
<i>-Gosh, she took her out.</i>
<i>-Han-ju took a hit.</i>

1056
00:47:05,697 --> 00:47:07,199
-<i>Hyun-seo!</i>
-Wow,

1057
00:47:07,282 --> 00:47:09,201
-what a sniper.
-Indeed.

1058
00:47:12,329 --> 00:47:13,247
Did you take her out?

1059
00:47:13,830 --> 00:47:15,082
What?

1060
00:47:15,165 --> 00:47:20,128
To be honest, my plan was to be
the soft woman.

1061
00:47:20,712 --> 00:47:22,589
-Shall we circle around?
-Okay.

1062
00:47:22,673 --> 00:47:24,550
He's coming from the back.

1063
00:47:25,509 --> 00:47:27,761
Team Mint is coming in our direction.

1064
00:47:29,596 --> 00:47:30,973
Watch out for Team Mint!

1065
00:47:31,056 --> 00:47:32,599
Look as you dodge.

1066
00:47:36,603 --> 00:47:39,022
But I was too into it.

1067
00:47:39,106 --> 00:47:41,275
I went a little too hard,

1068
00:47:41,358 --> 00:47:42,526
which I kind of regret doing.

1069
00:47:43,527 --> 00:47:46,905
Because men like it

1070
00:47:46,989 --> 00:47:50,200
<i>when women seem to need their protection.</i>

1071
00:47:50,284 --> 00:47:53,495
I may have failed to trigger
his protective instinct.

1072
00:47:54,162 --> 00:47:55,872
<i>It was a shame.</i>

1073
00:47:57,249 --> 00:47:59,293
Mad respect for Hyun-seo.

1074
00:48:01,295 --> 00:48:04,131
<i>I couldn't believe</i>
<i>that Hyun-seo ran into the battlefield.</i>

1075
00:48:04,214 --> 00:48:07,175
<i>She looks quite delicate on the outside,</i>

1076
00:48:07,259 --> 00:48:10,012
and she didn't seem like the active type.

1077
00:48:10,095 --> 00:48:13,015
But back there,
I saw she's got some serious grit.

1078
00:48:13,098 --> 00:48:14,725
He must've found that charming.

1079
00:48:14,808 --> 00:48:16,310
He's basically her fanboy now.

1080
00:48:17,644 --> 00:48:18,854
I'm so exhausted.

1081
00:48:24,359 --> 00:48:27,362
HYUK-JOON, HYUN-SEO

1082
00:48:27,446 --> 00:48:28,280
But…

1083
00:48:28,363 --> 00:48:30,532
SOO-HYUN, JIN-WOO

1084
00:48:30,616 --> 00:48:31,742
-Would you stand behind me?
-Okay.

1085
00:48:31,825 --> 00:48:34,828
JIN-WOO, SOO-HYUN

1086
00:48:37,789 --> 00:48:39,249
I got hit in my head.

1087
00:48:39,333 --> 00:48:40,334
Get behind me.

1088
00:48:43,837 --> 00:48:44,921
This way.

1089
00:48:45,005 --> 00:48:46,465
-To the back.
-Back?

1090
00:48:46,548 --> 00:48:47,591
To the bushes.

1091
00:48:48,884 --> 00:48:50,510
<i>You know,</i>

1092
00:48:50,594 --> 00:48:53,639
taking a bullet on an area
outside the protective gear

1093
00:48:53,722 --> 00:48:55,515
was a bit painful.

1094
00:48:55,599 --> 00:48:57,559
<i>But when Jin-woo saw</i>
<i>the bullets coming our way,</i>

1095
00:48:57,643 --> 00:48:59,019
<i>he told me to get behind him</i>

1096
00:48:59,102 --> 00:49:02,147
<i>even though he could've gotten hit</i>
<i>on the uncovered areas as well.</i>

1097
00:49:02,230 --> 00:49:04,524
So I was moved by that.

1098
00:49:05,025 --> 00:49:06,985
Jin-woo does seem quite reliable.

1099
00:49:07,069 --> 00:49:08,945
That's how it should be.
But Jung-yun went, "Oh, it stings!"

1100
00:49:09,029 --> 00:49:10,238
"Oh, it stings!"

1101
00:49:10,322 --> 00:49:12,908
-Jin-woo covered her like this.
-Right, he did that.

1102
00:49:12,991 --> 00:49:15,077
-That's what we wanted to see.
-He's cool.

1103
00:49:15,661 --> 00:49:16,745
Oh, I'm out of bullets.

1104
00:49:17,412 --> 00:49:18,914
-Are you out of bullets?
-Yes.

1105
00:49:23,585 --> 00:49:25,837
-Shall I go and get more ammunition?
-Now?

1106
00:49:26,546 --> 00:49:27,756
-Can you make it quick?
-What?

1107
00:49:27,839 --> 00:49:29,383
-Make it quick.
-I'll be back.

1108
00:49:41,812 --> 00:49:43,563
<i>-Oh, no.</i>
<i>-My goodness.</i>

1109
00:49:43,647 --> 00:49:44,564
<i>He spilled all of them!</i>

1110
00:49:48,110 --> 00:49:49,152
The magazine was open.

1111
00:49:50,404 --> 00:49:51,530
-I need to go again.
-What?

1112
00:49:52,239 --> 00:49:53,532
-Again?
-I spilled it all.

1113
00:49:54,324 --> 00:49:57,077
-I don't know where Soo-hyun is.
-She's hiding in there.

1114
00:49:57,160 --> 00:49:58,954
We'll need to circle around.

1115
00:49:59,037 --> 00:50:00,372
-Shall we do that?
-Yes.

1116
00:50:02,416 --> 00:50:04,835
<i>They're circling around.</i>

1117
00:50:04,918 --> 00:50:06,420
HYUN-SEO

1118
00:50:06,503 --> 00:50:07,796
<i>They have great teamwork.</i>

1119
00:50:09,214 --> 00:50:11,007
Shall we go? I'll go this way.

1120
00:50:11,091 --> 00:50:12,134
-Okay.
-Get ammunition.

1121
00:50:13,051 --> 00:50:15,137
<i>Okay. Be careful.</i>

1122
00:50:18,056 --> 00:50:21,059
SOO-HYUN, HYUK-JOON

1123
00:50:27,190 --> 00:50:28,775
-Why shoot so much?
-Don't shoot so much!

1124
00:50:28,859 --> 00:50:30,527
-Stop shooting! Hey!
-Stop shooting!

1125
00:50:30,610 --> 00:50:31,903
-Hey!
-Stop shooting!

1126
00:50:31,987 --> 00:50:34,614
Why is he blasting like that?

1127
00:50:34,698 --> 00:50:36,324
A single hit is all you need.

1128
00:50:36,408 --> 00:50:38,034
-They got carried away. Hyun-seo…
-Hyuk-joon!

1129
00:50:38,118 --> 00:50:40,454
-He and Hyun-seo are too into it.
-That's too much.

1130
00:50:40,537 --> 00:50:41,955
I'm sorry,

1131
00:50:42,456 --> 00:50:43,665
but he looks like a lunatic.

1132
00:50:45,584 --> 00:50:47,419
What's wrong with that team?

1133
00:50:47,502 --> 00:50:49,880
It's a dead giveaway
that Hyuk-joon has never dated.

1134
00:50:49,963 --> 00:50:52,340
-It was like <i>Taken</i>. It was that intense.
-I know.

1135
00:50:52,424 --> 00:50:54,259
Seriously. Soo-hyun's top pick
was Hyuk-joon.

1136
00:50:54,342 --> 00:50:55,469
I know. That was…

1137
00:50:55,552 --> 00:50:58,013
Soo-hyun will lose feelings
for Hyuk-joon after that.

1138
00:50:59,639 --> 00:51:01,433
<i>He's in a proper stance too.</i>

1139
00:51:01,516 --> 00:51:03,852
JIN-WOO AND SOO-HYUN ARE OUT

1140
00:51:04,478 --> 00:51:05,312
Finished.

1141
00:51:06,188 --> 00:51:07,022
KIM SOO-HYUN
TOP PICK: HYUK-JOON

1142
00:51:07,105 --> 00:51:08,190
I was seriously upset.

1143
00:51:08,273 --> 00:51:10,901
You know, he chased me down

1144
00:51:10,984 --> 00:51:12,819
to take me out.

1145
00:51:12,903 --> 00:51:15,113
<i>It was completely unnecessary.</i>

1146
00:51:15,197 --> 00:51:18,825
<i>He only needed to shoot once or twice,</i>
<i>but he just kept going.</i>

1147
00:51:18,909 --> 00:51:21,244
It was uncalled for.

1148
00:51:21,328 --> 00:51:22,829
My top pick is…

1149
00:51:22,913 --> 00:51:25,624
With how things are now, it's Jin-woo.

1150
00:51:26,666 --> 00:51:28,376
We made the best team.

1151
00:51:28,460 --> 00:51:30,295
I knew we'd make a great team.

1152
00:51:30,378 --> 00:51:32,088
HYUK-JOON, HYUN-SEO

1153
00:51:32,172 --> 00:51:34,758
<i>We had incredible teamwork.</i>

1154
00:51:34,841 --> 00:51:36,843
We didn't talk much,

1155
00:51:36,927 --> 00:51:39,012
<i>but we knew what to do.</i>

1156
00:51:39,095 --> 00:51:43,266
Also, Hyuk-joon stood like this
when bullets flew our way

1157
00:51:43,350 --> 00:51:46,228
<i>and protected me. I was so thankful.</i>

1158
00:51:46,311 --> 00:51:49,898
My heart fluttered a bit.
He was very kind.

1159
00:51:49,981 --> 00:51:53,735
The most memorable moment was
when we took first place.

1160
00:51:53,819 --> 00:51:55,487
And… Oh, I take that back.

1161
00:51:56,238 --> 00:51:58,031
It was when I taught her how to shoulder.

1162
00:51:59,449 --> 00:52:01,827
Then shoulder the rifle.

1163
00:52:03,411 --> 00:52:05,747
-You don't disappoint.
-It becomes more stable.

1164
00:52:05,831 --> 00:52:08,333
<i>When I taught her that,</i>

1165
00:52:08,416 --> 00:52:10,126
we were standing close.

1166
00:52:10,210 --> 00:52:14,130
We weren't touching physically,
but our bodies got close.

1167
00:52:14,214 --> 00:52:16,091
It gave me butterflies.

1168
00:52:16,174 --> 00:52:18,134
Through the paintball date…

1169
00:52:18,718 --> 00:52:19,636
How should I put it?

1170
00:52:19,719 --> 00:52:21,805
<i>I don't know how to describe this feeling.</i>

1171
00:52:21,888 --> 00:52:25,100
<i>I felt that achieving something together</i>

1172
00:52:25,183 --> 00:52:26,893
<i>was an impressive feat.</i>

1173
00:52:27,519 --> 00:52:31,815
It made me think it'd be fun
to do another activity with her.

1174
00:52:31,898 --> 00:52:33,608
It got me excited.

1175
00:52:33,692 --> 00:52:36,444
-It was very nice.
-Yes.

1176
00:52:38,238 --> 00:52:40,657
<i>-They seem very compatible.</i>
<i>-You're right.</i>

1177
00:52:40,740 --> 00:52:42,492
-That was the picture we wanted.
-Yes.

1178
00:52:42,576 --> 00:52:47,080
The atmosphere definitely changed
after the paintball date.

1179
00:52:47,163 --> 00:52:50,083
-Soo-hyun's top pick was Hyuk-joon,
-That's right.

1180
00:52:50,166 --> 00:52:51,418
but now it's Jin-woo.

1181
00:52:51,501 --> 00:52:55,422
Hyuk-joon and Hyun-seo
definitely developed feelings

1182
00:52:55,505 --> 00:52:56,756
-for each other.
-They did.

1183
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:59,217
That's right.
Their feelings are growing stronger.

1184
00:52:59,301 --> 00:53:01,553
<i>-Hello.</i>
<i>-Hello.</i>

1185
00:53:01,636 --> 00:53:02,721
<i>Let's get going now.</i>

1186
00:53:06,516 --> 00:53:08,560
Do you have strong insteps?

1187
00:53:08,643 --> 00:53:10,770
-What was that? My foot?
-The top of your foot.

1188
00:53:10,854 --> 00:53:12,939
-Will we step on each other's feet?
-We might.

1189
00:53:13,023 --> 00:53:15,191
-Is that so? But…
-"We might."

1190
00:53:15,275 --> 00:53:16,902
-it won't be a problem.
-Really?

1191
00:53:16,985 --> 00:53:18,361
One time in the past…

1192
00:53:18,445 --> 00:53:19,321
-Well…
-Thank goodness.

1193
00:53:19,404 --> 00:53:20,822
My foot got stepped on by a horse's hoof.

1194
00:53:20,906 --> 00:53:22,282
-What?
-But…

1195
00:53:22,365 --> 00:53:24,034
-But I was fine.
-Really?

1196
00:53:24,451 --> 00:53:25,911
I'm surprised that you were fine.

1197
00:53:26,578 --> 00:53:28,371
-You have iron feet.
-Yeah.

1198
00:53:28,455 --> 00:53:30,206
Why is Jae-seo sitting like some chairman?

1199
00:53:30,290 --> 00:53:31,958
Seriously, Jae-seo…

1200
00:53:32,042 --> 00:53:35,045
He works on computers a lot,
so he has a bit of forward head posture.

1201
00:53:35,128 --> 00:53:36,922
Straighten your neck like this, Jae-seo.

1202
00:53:37,589 --> 00:53:39,507
I'd like to fold his collar for him.

1203
00:53:41,384 --> 00:53:43,929
At this point, is there someone

1204
00:53:44,012 --> 00:53:47,182
-you're interested in
-Yes?

1205
00:53:47,265 --> 00:53:50,477
or want to get to know better?

1206
00:53:50,560 --> 00:53:51,561
Yes, there is.

1207
00:53:52,479 --> 00:53:53,480
There is someone.

1208
00:53:54,439 --> 00:53:57,484
Of course, it's not like I'm in love yet.

1209
00:53:57,567 --> 00:53:59,319
My feelings are slowly getting stronger.

1210
00:53:59,402 --> 00:54:01,655
At first, I didn't particularly
feel strongly toward anyone.

1211
00:54:01,738 --> 00:54:03,615
But now, I definitely
like this person more.

1212
00:54:04,824 --> 00:54:06,743
<i>I wanted to talk to Seo-yoon,</i>

1213
